<TEXT>
the battle over who will succeed 
87yearold john c stennis to the us senate has been punctuated 
with cries of let george go a reference to the man paid 
50000 a year to chauffer and protect house minority whip trent 
lott in washington 
democrat wayne dowdy launched his campaign against lott by 
focusing on the employee george awkward whose salary is almost 
five times the average farm income and more than three times the 
average family income in this dirtpoor state 
in his bid to retain a senate seat for the democrats dowdy has 
urged lott to let george go and said that before we cut 
services to our senior citizens in mississippi lets cut george 
to combat the dowdy campaign lott has reminded his democratic 
opponent and house colleague that funds for the bodyguards 
accorded most of the congressional leadership were in a bill 
dowdy voted for and lott opposed 
further awkward was featured in a lott television commercial 
pointedly telling the democrat mr dowdy im nobodys 
chauffeur got it 
but beyond a squabble over perks in the nations capital is a 
deeper struggle between two young veteran politicians of markedly 
different philosophies whoever is elected an era in mississippi 
politics will end 
there has been only one new us senator elected in mississippi 
since 1947 when stennis won election the late sen james o 
eastland also a democrat preceded stennis in the senate by five 
years 
when eastland retired in 1978 republican thad cochran was 
elected as the states first gop senator since reconstruction 
lott from the conservative 5th congressional district in southern 
mississippi is hoping stennis retirement a decade later due to 
declining health will give him the same chance to advance 
lott was elected in 1972 to succeed his onetime employer on 
capitol hill the late rep william colmer when the democrat 
retired the 46yearold lawyer was elected minority whip in 1980 
as a member of the house judiciary committee in his first term 
lott staunchly defended richard nixon during his impeachment 
hearings the exposure pushed lott to the leadership of the 
conservative wing of the republican party 
lott voted for the 1986 tax reform act and has repeatedly voted 
for aid to the contra and angola rebels he also has voted to put 
limits on the clean water act against efforts to limit star wars 
funding and against sanctions against the whiteminority government 
of south africa 
despite his strict conservative voting record he has preferred 
to stress while campaigning his backing of employment and economic 
development programs in general terms 
dowdy has sharply criticized lott for voting to cut funding for 
social programs including votes on social securty medicaid 
welfare issues all of which provide support for a large number of 
poor mississippians both black and white 
the republican has countered that when the chips were down 
that is in final consideration of legislation he successfully 
fought efforts to bail out the budget by using social security 
funds the record appears to bear that out 
dowdy was a folksy smalltown mayor in mccomb when he was voted 
into congress in a closely fought special election he was the 
first democrat elected to that post since 1972 
the 45yearold dowdys congressional district is dominated by 
the capital city of jackson a republican stronghold for decades 
but the rural sections of the southwestern part of the state with 
their large black voting population propelled dowdy to 
reelections in 1982 1984 and 1986 
lott has tried to pin on dowdy the label of a tax and spend 
liberal he has cited dowdy for what he has called a liberal voting 
record and for his votes against reagan administration efforts to 
reduce federal spending 
at the neshoba county fair in philadelphia miss lott asked a 
crowd whether they wanted a senator that is going to follow in 
the line of mcgovern mondale oneill wright jackson and 
dukakis 
dowdys voting record generally has followed party lines he 
voted against the reagan tax cut and against on limits on the clean 
water act he also voted for sanctions against the south african 
government and for aid to the contra rebels and for limits on the 
star wars program he was against aid to the angola rebels 
