du pont co says it will spend more than 25 
million to begin commercial production in 1990 of a substitute for 
the chemical in auto air conditioners that is considered one of the 
most culpable substances in destroying the earths ozone layer 
the company said thursday it will install a unit at its corpus 
christi texas plant to make hfc134a a shortlived fluorocarbon 
containing no chlorine that the company intends to sell for the 
refrigeration uses of cfc12 one of the chlorofluorocarbon or cfc 
compounds 
du pont is taking a significant risk but a risk our board of 
directors insists we take in deciding on production before the 
completion of toxicity testing said joseph p glas director of du 
ponts freon products division 
since it contains no chlorine the new compound has no effect on 
the ozone layer that keeps those cancercausing rays from reaching 
the surface of the earth when it breaks up in the atmosphere 
it takes the powerful ultraviolet rays of the sun normally 
shielded by ozone high in the stratosphere to break up cfc 
molecules which liberate their chlorine to attack the ozone 
major producing nations agreed last year to cut cfc production 
by 50 percent in 1998 but the environmental protection agency said 
monday its latest analyses show the compounds should be banned 
around the world 
