<TEXT>
new york cartoonist charles addams whose macabre characters 
and morbid humor haunted the pages of the new yorker magazine for 
half a century and spawned the addams family tv show of the 
1960s has died he was 76 
addams died thursday in the emergency room at st clares 
hospital and health center said mary alice gregg a hospital 
administrator 
he suffered a heart attack in his car in front of his manhattan 
apartment building said his wife marilyn 
hes always been a car buff so it was a nice way to go 
said mrs addams who married her husband in a pet cemetery in 1980 
he thought it would be nice and cheerful she said of the 
wedding 
his first cartoon was published in the new yorker in 1935 but 
his first major one was published there on jan 13 1940 it showed 
a woman skier whose tracks passed neatly but inexplicably on both 
sides of a large tree 
i cant imagine the magazine without him said robert 
gottlieb the magazines editor 
addams born in westfield nj doodled skulls and bones for 
his high school newspaper before studying further at colgate 
university the university of pennsylvania and the grand central 
school of art in new york 
his ghoulish characters whose rundown victorian mansion was 
crowded with infernal devices and lurking creatures was the 
inspiration for the addams family television show of the 1960s 
the addamses from morticia the blackgowned matriarch to lurch 
the giant butler and thing a hand that popped out of a box were 
directly inspired by addams cartoons 
addams has produced 10 cartoon collections that have together 
sold more than 460000 copies 
the new york times art critic john russell called addams an 
american landmark one of the few by which one and all have learned 
to steer 
but russell said ghouls and ghosts are not the whole of 
addams the jokes are so good that we do not notice the sturdiness 
of the line the rocksolid composition the eye for scale and 
placement the calculated ordinariness that lures us into the 
trap 
some of addams cartoons take a moment to figure out 
in one a bus driver looks disquieted because the next stop 
buzzer has just been pulled after a moment the reader usually 
notices that the bus is approaching a rainswept graveyard and no 
one but the driver is on board 
in another four scouts cross a brook on a fallen tree carrying 
a banner that says beaver patrol each of the scouts has buck 
teeth and the reader is left to wonder whether the tree fell 
because of beavers or the patrol 
although he profited immensely from his work addams said he did 
not reap large direct benefits from the television show 
they gave me money each week but after the first runs ended i 
didnt get anything no residuals this was a mistake made by the 
big old fat law firm i let represent me addams once said 
john ohara a friend of addams said his drawings belied his 
personality 
i dont think hed hurt a fly he said i never have seen 
him lose his temper although that is not to say he doesnt get 
mad he happens to be what is called easygoing and has a decent 
contempt for the opinions of mankind 
new yorker spokeswoman rhonda pinzer said the magazine still has 
some covers and cartoons that addams had submitted and probably 
will run in the future 
mrs addams said the funeral would be private 
</TEXT>
