<TEXT>
here are high points of the reforms communist 
party chief mikhail s gorbachev is seeking in the soviet political 
system and party apparatus which party leaders and lawmakers will 
reportedly consider this week 
</TEXT>
<TEXT>
a stronger presidency apparently desiring a government post 
tailored to his own talents gorbachev has called for giving the 
soviet president responsibility over defense and foreign policy and 
power to name the prime minister president andrei a gromyko now 
head of state holds an essentially ceremonial job 
</TEXT>
<TEXT>
a more active legislature gorbachev wants the 1500member 
supreme soviet the countrys nominal parliament merged with a new 
750seat body representing artists labor union members and other 
social groups that assembly would then elect a fulltime 
parliament of 400 or so members who would have real powers to pass 
a state budget and other laws 
</TEXT>
<TEXT>
multicandidate elections the soviet leader wants voters 
nationwide for the first time to have a choice of candidates in 
elections to the expanded supreme soviet by next march it is 
likely however that the communist party would keep its power of 
veto over individual candidacies 
</TEXT>
<TEXT>
a slimmeddown party gorbachev wants the partys 20million 
membership roll reduced and its apparatus trimmed those goals are 
in line with his often stated desire to more clearly delineate 
party and government responsibilities 
</TEXT>
<TEXT>
indirect control on party bosses gorbachev wants local party 
chiefs to run for their local legislatures and be elected to be 
their chairmen if they fail to win either election because of a 
lack of popular support they could lose their party post as well 
the partys central committee adopted broad goals for political 
reform on july 29 after hearing gorbachev outline his agenda those 
decisions however were never made public and could differ from 
the reforms sought by gorbachev 
the soviet leader has said changes are needed in the countrys 
political system to prevent any repeat of the bloody repression 
carried out under josef v stalin or the corruption and stagnation 
now seen as endemic under leonid i brezhnev 
</TEXT>
</DOC>

