aids the deadly disease that allows other 
infections to ravage the body is believed responsible for an 
increase in pneumonia deaths among young adults in new york and 
possibly other cities 
the national centers for disease control reported thursday that 
the mortality rate for men 2544 from pneumonia increased in new 
york from four deaths per 100000 people in 1978 before the advent 
of aids to 19 per 100000 in 1987 
for women the rate increased from two per 100000 in 1978 to 
seven in 1987 actual fatality counts were not included in the cdc 
report 
most pneumoniaattributable deaths occur among the elderly 
the cdc said in its weekly report in new york city however the 
number and rate of such deaths among younger persons have increased 
in association with aids infections in intravenous drug abusers 
the records of 192 new yorkers ages 2544 who died with 
pneumonia in 1986 showed that 153 or 80 percent were at high risk 
for aids including 126 intravenous drug abusers fifty had 
possible symptoms of aids and 26 were diagnosed as having aids 
