here is the schedule for discovery 
astronauts through missions end all times edt 
saturday 
437 am crew awakens exercises and eats breakfast followed 
by spacecraft systems checks and experiments testing an infrared 
communications system and photographing lightning in the atmosphere 
742 am photograph the horizon at sunrise 
1107 am and 1227 pm photograph crystal growth 
experiments 
102 pm meal 
212 pm rehearse reentry procedures including donning 
pressure suits and installing emergency escape system 
442 pm protein crystal growth experiment 
607 pm meal 
737 pm begin 8hour sleep 
sunday 
337 am crew awakens exercises eats breakfast and checks 
spacecraft systems 
442 am turn off materials processing furnace 
642 am cell separation experiment 
827 am commander and pilot check flight control system for 
reentry 
1037 am crew holds news conference answering questions 
relayed by mission control 
1207 pm meal 
107 pm equipment stowed to prepare for reentry 
622 pm turn on materials processing furnace 
630 pm meal 
737 pm begin 8hour sleep 
monday 
337 am crew awakens eats breakfast and checks spacecraft 
systems 
502 am turn off experiments 
854 am close payload bay doors 
924 am astronauts don pressure suits 
1131 am ignite engines to start return to earth 
