saints headed by the 89yearold benson a former us agriculture 
secretary 
the vacancy was created may 20 at the death at age 90 of marion 
g romney the quorums president he was replaced by the 
nextmostsenior member of the twelve howard w hunter next in 
line to be church president 
vacancies in the allmale hierarchy usually are filled during 
the general conferences held on the first weekends of april and 
october 
the twoday conference is held in the 6000seat tabernacle on 
temple square but hundreds of thousands more will view the 
sessions on television and over the churchs satellite network the 
latter reaches more than 2000 church centers in the united states 
canada and puerto rico 
the church has 65 million members and missionaries in 80 
countries and 17 territories 
