lose that job at saturdays supreme soviet session 
removal of those officials left only two pregorbachev 
appointees on the politburo vitaly i vorotnikov chief of the 
russian republic and vladimir v shcherbitsky head of the 
ukraine the ruling body dropped from 13 to 12 members 
one official brought to moscow by gorbachev anatoly f 
dobrynin former ambassador to the united states also retired as a 
secretary of the party central committee 
