they forgot that its normal said raab 
it was a failed joint that led to the jan 28 1986 challenger 
destruction killing seven astronauts a presidential commission 
that investigated the accident found that rubberized orings did 
not seal allowing flame to escape 
to return the grounded shuttle fleet to space as soon as 
possible the national aeronautics and space administration chose 
to redesign the challengerstyle boosters a process that took 32 
months instead of the four to five years required to develop an 
entirely new design 
nasa made 145 changes and then subjected the boosters to the 
most rigorous testing program ever conducted for solidfueled 
rockets 
the boosters are the largest solidfueled rockets ever built 
loaded with 11 million pounds of propellant each booster 
weighs 13 million pounds and produces 33 million pounds of 
thrust the two boosters used in each shuttle launch provide 80 
percent of the power need to reach orbit 
