<TEXT>
union station a magnificent beaux arts 
structure that welcomed train travelers to the nations capital for 
a halfcentury before crumbling into decay in the 1950s came back 
to life on thursday 
today were proud to give you a building brought back to life 
by american business at its best and government at its best union 
station is a train station again said stuart scott president of 
lasalle partners ltd which supervised the 160 million 
rehabilitation project 
more than 100000 red white and blue balloons were released 
confetti rained down and the whistle of an 80yearold steam 
engine blasted as officials swung open the mahogany doors of the 
immense structure and a crowd of thousands swarmed inside 
its magnificent said transportation secretary jim burnley 
were looking at a complete 180degree reversal of the problems 
caused by government incompetence in past projects involving the 
station 
union station had fallen into neglect with the decline in train 
ridership in the 50s and was destined for the wrecking ball when 
it was designated a national landmark in 1964 
the nixon administration spent 48 million trying to convert the 
station into a national visitors center for the nations 
bicentennial in 1976 but the project failed and the doors swung 
shut 
cobwebs gathered in the corners and toadstools sprang up in the 
dirt on the floor over the years train travelers have been 
reaching the capitals amtrak station by way of a temporary walkway 
along the west side of the building 
in 1981 president reagan signed the union station redevelopment 
act which called on the private sector to manage another 
restoration launching the beginning of a sevenyear effort 
the federal government has demonstrated a remarkable level of 
incompetence in years gone by said burnley and we were 
determined that it was going to be done right this time 
the redevelopment team la salle a national real estate firm 
williams jackson ewing a retail developer and leaser and 
architect benjamin thompson amp associates of boston patterned the 
renovation on original architect daniel hudson burnhams 1907 
design 
those who attended the opening many of them employees from 
nearby capitol hill offices strolled through the airy shopping 
mall admiring the high vaulted ceiling with its etched gold finish 
the massive sunfilled main hall of the structure resembles a 
museum with high balconies framing romanstyle statues and arched 
windows 
amtrak has 22 ticket counters and a baggage carousel in the mall 
area some 210000 square feet of retail space will houses many 
upscale shops and a string of restaurants a ninescreen 
2000seat movie theatre is scheduled to open in november 
the district of columbia government is building a parking garage 
for 1500 cars with 40 million in federal highway money lack of 
parking was considered one reason for the failure of the earlier 
renovation effort 
officials are optimistic that with more than 33000 subway 
commuters and 8400 amtrak passengers using the station daily 
combined with the thousands of people who work nearby the new 
union station will be a success 
</TEXT>
