are in nicaragua 
us district judge george p kazens ruling issued friday 
limits the scope of the international emergency economic powers 
act the basis for the reagan administrations economic embargo of 
nicaragua 
the act contains an exemption for humanitarian aid the reagan 
administration had been interpreting it on a casebycase basis 
the court said and refusing to allow export of certain items 
including cars and trucks 
kazens ruling said because of the exemption in the economic 
powers act the president has no authority to regulate or prohibit 
us citizens donations to foreign countries which the donor 
intends to be used to relieve human suffering 
specifically the foreign assets control office part of the 
treasury department cannot require donors to get licenses before 
exporting such aid kazen said the act was cited when the office 
temporarily barred the veterans donation of vehicles to nicaraguan 
schools hospitals and churches 
