saudi arabia the largest producer in the organization of 
petroleum exporting countries has taken the lead in the past in 
bringing other members back to their assigned quotas 
saudi arabia is said to have recently joined the united arab 
emirates kuwait and iraq in exceeding their quota leading to 
speculation that the saudis are trying a new strategy to force opec 
members to rein in oil production 
