<TEXT>
wheat futures prices closed modestly higher but 
corn oats and soybeans finished mixed friday on the chicago board 
of trade in cautious trading ahead of the agriculture departments 
report on us grain stocks 
analysts attributed virtually all the activity to 
positionbalancing in advance of the quarterly grain stocks report 
i didnt hear a thing about any other factors that 
influenced trading during the session said steve freed grain 
market analyst with dean witter reynolds inc in chicago 
the report showed soybean stocks at 302 million bushels down 
from 655 million in the june report and 436 million a year earlier 
the usda estimated corn stocks at 426 billion bushels down 
from 583 billion on june 1 and 488 billion a year earlier 
wheat stocks were estimated at 224 billion bushels compared 
with 127 billion in june and 296 billion a year earlier 
the soybean figure was well above most prereport estimates and 
traders pronounced it bearish for soybean prices the corn and 
wheat figures fell at the low end of prereport estimates and were 
said to be bullish 
at the close wheat was 1 cents to 3 cents higher with the 
contract for delivery in december at 414 a bushel corn was 1 
cents lower to 1 cents higher with december at 286 a bushel 
oats were 4 cents lower to cent higher with december at 241 a 
bushel soybeans were 2 cents lower to 6 cents higher with 
november at 812 a bushel 
