<DOCNO> AP880930-0254 </DOCNO>
<TEXT>
zenith electronics corp sued thursday 
to block an investment groups attempt to wage a battle for control 
of the company and contended the group only was interested in 
boosting the price of its stock 
the company filed a federal lawsuit in chicago to prohibit the 
group brookhurst partners from waging a proxy fight against 
zenith management until it completely and accurately complied with 
federal disclosure requirements and from disseminating documents 
relating to any offer to buy zenith 
the suit also seeks a declaration that zenith may refuse to 
recognize the results of any proxy vote or any purchases of its 
stock by brookhurst until 30 days after the defendants comply with 
federal disclosure requirements 
brookhurst which controls 61 percent of zeniths stock and is 
the companys biggest shareholder is attempting to wage a proxy 
fight to force the sale of zenith the last us maker of 
televisions 
the partnership on thursday filed a motion in delaware chancery 
court seeking the elimination of zenith bylaws that restrict the 
rights of stockholders to act by written consent 
the motion also seeks the elimination of zeniths stockholder 
rights plan a socalled poison pill designed to deter hostile 
takeovers by diluting the value of a companys holdings 
the stockholder rights plan gives zenith the right to exercise 
its takeover defense if any one shareholder gains written consent 
from 15 percent of the shares 
brookhurst also wants copies of the zeniths shareholder lists 
and financial records 
a hearing is scheduled for oct 5 in chancery court concerning 
the shareholder lists 
brookhurst filed the motion in state court one day after a 
federal judge dismissed the groups federal suit which contained 
similar complaints on jurisdictional grounds 
brookhurst is seeking shareholder consent to trim zeniths board 
from 10 directors to six and to fill three of those seats with 
nominees committed to selling zenith 
zeniths lawsuit claimed brookhurst partners had deliberately 
conveyed the false impression that they are planning to acquire 
or broker the acquisition of zenith or some portion of its 
business 
zenith contends brookhurst actually seeks to artificially 
inflate the price of zeniths stock by creating the impression that 
zenith is in play so members of the group can sell their 
shares at a quick profit 
brookhurst said in a statement that zeniths lawsuit was 
groundless and reiterated its call for zeniths management to 
detail its plans for returning the battered company to profitablity 
unless zenith reveals such a plan the dissidents said they 
would continue their drive to sell the company 
</TEXT>
</DOC>

